      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 200°C. Lay out the bacon strips flat on a roasting tray. Wrap each one around a chipolata, starting at one end and working your way down to the other. Wrap at a slight angle and make sure you cover as much of the sausage as you can."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slide into the oven for 15-20 mins until the bacon is starting to crisp. Meanwhile, mix the honey and hot sauce together in a small bowl. Once the pigs are starting to crisp, brush with the honey mixture and return to the oven for 2-3 mins. Repeat a few times until golden and sticky. Serve!"
    }
